candidates.body:
Updates the requirements on [hashbrown](https://github.com/rust-lang/hashbrown) to permit the latest version.
Changelog

Sourced from hashbrown's changelog.

[v0.13.1] - 2022-11-10

Added

  • Added Equivalent trait to customize key lookups. (#350)
  • Added support for 16-bit targets. (#368)
  • Added RawTable::allocation_info which provides information about the memory usage of a table. (#371)

Changed

  • Bumped MSRV to 1.61.0.
  • Upgraded to ahash 0.8. (#357)
  • Make with_hasher_in const. (#355)
  • The following methods have been removed from the RawTable API in favor of safer alternatives:
    • RawTable::erase_no_drop => Use RawTable::erase or RawTable::remove instead.
    • Bucket::read => Use RawTable::remove instead.
    • Bucket::drop => Use RawTable::erase instead.
    • Bucket::write => Use Bucket::as_mut instead.

Fixed

  • Ensure that HashMap allocations don't exceed isize::MAX. (#362)
  • Fixed issue with field retagging in scopeguard. (#359)

[v0.12.3] - 2022-07-17

Fixed

  • Fixed double-drop in RawTable::clone_from. (#348)

[v0.12.2] - 2022-07-09

Added

  • Added Entry API for HashSet. (#342)
  • Added Extend<&'a (K, V)> for HashMap<K, V, S, A>. (#340)
  • Added length-based short-circuiting for hash table iteration. (#338)
  • Added a function to access the RawTable of a HashMap. (#335)

Changed

  • Edited do_alloc to reduce LLVM IR generated. (#341)

[v0.12.1] - 2022-05-02

Fixed

candidates.title: feat: private backpointer
candidates.body:
Private backpointers as according to the spec: https://github.com/wnfs-wg/spec/blob/main/spec/private-wnfs.md#313-node-previous-backlinks

TLDR:
```diff
type PrivateDirectory = {
  type: "wnfs/priv/dir"
  version: "0.2.0"
  // encrypted using deriveKey(ratchet)
  header: Encrypted<CBOR<PrivateNodeHeader>>
+++  // encrypted using deriveKey(previousRatchet) where inc(previousRatchet) = ratchet
+++  previous: Encrypted<CBOR<Array<CID>>>

  // USERLAND
  ...
}
```

Three critical points in the code:
1. The places where we previously called `advance_ratchet`, we now need to do something extra: Before we advance the ratchet, we need to "have remembered" the CID that the directory/node was stored as and add that to the previous links *before* we advance the ratchet (so we can use the 'previous' revision key).
   This is mostly the `fix_up_path_nodes` function in `PrivateDirectory`.
2. `put` and `get` in the `PrivateForest`. This is where we last knew the `Cid` of node ciphertexts. Instead of throwing away the knowledge of the specific CID, we need to keep around this info (so we can use it in the places referred to in (1)).
   Effectively they get threaded through via `PrivateNode::load` and all the `deserialize_from_cbor` functions as the `from_cid: Cid` parameter.
3. In the previous iterators in `private/previous.rs` we need to resolve the bias passed to `PrivateForest::get` according to the decrypted previous links. I.e. when we look at the previous revision and there's multiple CIDs in the multivalue, just take the CID that matches one of the 'previous' CIDs.

TODO:
- [x] ~~Some code deduplication from multiple `store` implementations.~~ I think that's more involved and goes past only the `.store` implementation. `PrivateFile` and `PrivateDirectory` share a lot of common fields - they need to be refactored so the commonalities live together. May even turn into a spec change, as that'd may steer implementers into the right direction.
- [x] Everything I described in (3)
- [x] Rebasing / merging

```sh
error: all dependencies must have a version specified when publishing.
dependency `skip_ratchet` does not specify a version
Note: The published dependency will use the version from crates.io,
the `git` specification will be removed from the dependency declaration.
```
